Public Domain, from the British Library's collections, 2013

Travels through Virginia. From Theodor de Bry's 'America', Vol. I, 1590, after a drawing of John White - caption: 'The idol Kivvasa. (Kiwasa). Engraving of an idol, Kivvasa, seated in a circular tent made from segments of woven cane or matting. The image has hair tied in a knot above the head, has a four-strand necklace of beads around the neck. It is wearing a close fitting jerkin, open at the front, and fringed skin apron-skirt.'
